---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Uplift Modeling: Who to Persuade | Geet Purohit';
const description =
  'A causal uplift model (T-learner and X-learner meta-learners, evaluated with the Qini curve) that predicts the incremental effect of a marketing email, then sorts every customer into Persuadables, Sure Things, Lost Causes, and Sleeping Dogs. Live in-browser demo.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="up">
    <div class="up-container">
      <a class="back" href="/">← geetpurohit.com</a>

      <!-- ===== Header ===== -->
      <header class="up-head reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Project · Causal Inference</span>
        <h1 class="up-title">Who Should You <span class="grad-text">Persuade?</span></h1>
        <p class="up-lead">
          Most models predict <em>who will convert</em>. That is the wrong question for a
          marketing budget. What you actually want is <strong>who converts only because you
          reached them</strong>, the incremental lift, not the raw likelihood. This is an
          <strong>uplift model</strong>: it estimates the causal effect of sending an email on
          each customer, using <strong>T-learner and X-learner meta-learners</strong> validated
          with the <strong>Qini curve</strong>. It runs on a real randomized experiment, the
          <a href="https://blog.minethatdata.com/2008/03/minethatdata-e-mail-analytics-and-data.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hillstrom email dataset</a>
          of 64,000 customers.
        </p>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Python</span>
          <span class="tag">Causal Inference</span>
          <span class="tag">T-Learner</span>
          <span class="tag">X-Learner</span>
          <span class="tag">Qini / AUUC</span>
          <span class="tag">scikit-learn</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div id="placeholderBanner" class="banner" hidden>
        ⚠️ Demo is running on <strong>placeholder coefficients</strong>. Run
        <code>causal-uplift/train.py</code> to populate it with values learned from real data.
      </div>

      <!-- ===== Interactive demo ===== -->
      <section class="demo reveal" aria-labelledby="demoHead">
        <div class="demo-inner">
          <div class="demo-left">
            <h2 id="demoHead" class="block-h">Score a customer</h2>
            <p class="block-sub">
              Describe a customer and the model estimates their visit probability
              <em>with and without</em> the email, entirely in your browser. The gap between
              the two is the uplift: the part the email actually caused.
            </p>
            <form id="upForm" class="fields" autocomplete="off"><!-- inputs injected by JS --></form>
          </div>

          <div class="demo-right">
            <div class="verdict-card" id="verdictCard">
              <div class="verdict-quad" id="quad">-</div>
              <div class="verdict-action" id="action">-</div>
              <div class="probs">
                <div class="prob-col">
                  <div class="prob-num" id="pTreat">-</div>
                  <div class="prob-cap">visits <strong>if emailed</strong></div>
                </div>
                <div class="prob-op">−</div>
                <div class="prob-col">
                  <div class="prob-num" id="pCtrl">-</div>
                  <div class="prob-cap">visits <strong>if not</strong></div>
                </div>
                <div class="prob-op">=</div>
                <div class="prob-col">
                  <div class="prob-num uplift" id="pUplift">-</div>
                  <div class="prob-cap"><strong>uplift</strong> (causal)</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="upbar"><div class="upbar-zero"></div><div id="upbarFill" class="upbar-fill"></div></div>
            </div>

            <div class="quad-card">
              <div class="quad-head">The four kinds of customer</div>
              <div class="quad-grid">
                <div class="qcell" data-q="persuadable"><span>Persuadables</span><small>convert only if emailed. Target these.</small></div>
                <div class="qcell" data-q="sure"><span>Sure Things</span><small>convert anyway. Emailing is wasted spend.</small></div>
                <div class="qcell" data-q="lost"><span>Lost Causes</span><small>will not convert either way.</small></div>
                <div class="qcell" data-q="sleeping"><span>Sleeping Dogs</span><small>emailing makes them <em>less</em> likely. Leave alone.</small></div>
              </div>
              <p class="quad-foot">
                Uplift modeling exists to find the top-left box. Targeting by raw
                likelihood keeps paying to reach Sure Things and, worse, pokes Sleeping Dogs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ===== Results ===== -->
      <section class="results reveal">
        <h2 class="block-h">Does the model actually rank uplift?</h2>
        <div class="tiles">
          <div class="tile"><div id="mAte" class="tile-num">-</div><div class="tile-cap">Average lift <span>email vs no email</span></div></div>
          <div class="tile"><div id="mQt" class="tile-num">-</div><div class="tile-cap">Qini <span>T-learner</span></div></div>
          <div class="tile"><div id="mQx" class="tile-num">-</div><div class="tile-cap">Qini <span>X-learner challenger</span></div></div>
          <div class="tile"><div id="mN" class="tile-num">-</div><div class="tile-cap">Customers <span>randomized trial</span></div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="charts">
          <figure class="chart"><img src="/uplift/qini.png" alt="Qini curve" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Qini curve: incremental visits captured vs. fraction targeted. Above the diagonal means the model beats targeting at random.</figcaption></figure>
          <figure class="chart"><img src="/uplift/deciles.png" alt="Actual lift by predicted-uplift decile" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Actual visit lift by predicted-uplift decile. Monotonic and rising means the ranking is real, not noise.</figcaption></figure>
          <figure class="chart"><img src="/uplift/distribution.png" alt="Distribution of predicted uplift" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>Predicted uplift across all customers. Some are genuinely persuadable, some barely move, a few are negative.</figcaption></figure>
          <figure class="chart"><img src="/uplift/ate.png" alt="Treated vs control visit rate" loading="lazy" /><figcaption>The raw experiment: emailing lifts the average visit rate. Uplift modeling turns that average into a per-customer decision.</figcaption></figure>
        </div>
        <p id="chartsNote" class="charts-note" hidden>
          Charts appear after you run <code>train.py</code> (it writes them into <code>public/uplift/</code>).
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ===== Method ===== -->
      <section class="method reveal">
        <h2 class="block-h">How it works</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li><strong>A real experiment.</strong> Customers were randomly assigned to receive an email or not, so a simple difference in visit rates is already an unbiased causal effect. Randomization is what makes the uplift identifiable.</li>
          <li><strong>T-learner.</strong> Two models are fit: one on the treated group, one on the control group. The predicted uplift for a customer is the difference between what each model says, P(visit | emailed) minus P(visit | not emailed).</li>
          <li><strong>X-learner.</strong> A stronger challenger that imputes each customer's individual treatment effect and models it directly, which helps when the treated and control groups are unbalanced. Reported alongside as a Qini benchmark.</li>
          <li><strong>Qini curve.</strong> Accuracy is meaningless here (you never see both outcomes for one person). Instead the model is judged on whether ranking customers by predicted uplift captures more incremental visits per email than random, which is exactly what a Qini curve measures.</li>
          <li><strong>Decision.</strong> Each customer lands in one of four quadrants. The budget goes to Persuadables, and Sleeping Dogs get left alone.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="repo">
          <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/geetpurohit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View the code on GitHub →</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script>
    type Feature = {
      key: string; label: string; type: 'numeric' | 'binary' | 'categorical';
      input: { min?: number; max?: number; step?: number; default: number | string };
      categories?: { value: string; label: string }[];
    };

    const $ = (id: string) => document.getElementById(id)!;
    const sig = (z: number) => 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-z));

    async function main() {
      let data: any;
      try {
        const res = await fetch('/uplift/uplift.json', { cache: 'no-cache' });
        data = await res.json();
      } catch {
        return;
      }

      const feats: Feature[] = data.features;
      const enc = data.encoding;
      const thr = data.meta.response_threshold as number;

      if (typeof data.meta?.generated === 'string' && data.meta.generated.startsWith('placeholder')) {
        $('placeholderBanner').hidden = false;
        $('chartsNote').hidden = false;
      }

      const pct = (x: number) => (x * 100).toFixed(1) + '%';
      $('mAte').textContent = '+' + pct(data.meta.ate);
      $('mQt').textContent = data.metrics?.t_learner?.qini?.toFixed(3) ?? '-';
      $('mQx').textContent = data.metrics?.x_learner?.qini?.toFixed(3) ?? '-';
      $('mN').textContent = ((data.meta.n_train + data.meta.n_test) / 1000).toFixed(0) + 'k';

      document.querySelectorAll<HTMLImageElement>('.chart img').forEach((img) => {
        img.addEventListener('error', () => { (img.closest('.chart') as HTMLElement).style.display = 'none'; });
      });

      // Build inputs
      const form = $('upForm');
      form.innerHTML = feats.map((f) => {
        if (f.type === 'numeric') {
          const i = f.input as any;
          return `<label class="field">
            <span class="field-top"><span>${f.label}</span><output id="out_${f.key}"></output></span>
            <input type="range" id="in_${f.key}" min="${i.min}" max="${i.max}" step="${i.step}" value="${i.default}" />
          </label>`;
        }
        if (f.type === 'binary') {
          return `<label class="field field-toggle">
            <input type="checkbox" id="in_${f.key}" />
            <span>${f.label}</span>
          </label>`;
        }
        const opts = (f.categories || []).map((c) => `<option value="${c.value}">${c.label}</option>`).join('');
        return `<label class="field">
          <span class="field-top"><span>${f.label}</span></span>
          <select id="in_${f.key}" class="select">${opts}</select>
        </label>`;
      }).join('');

      feats.forEach((f) => {
        const el = $('in_' + f.key) as HTMLInputElement;
        if (f.type === 'categorical') el.value = String(f.input.default);
        el.addEventListener('input', compute);
        el.addEventListener('change', compute);
      });

      // Build the model column vector from the raw inputs (mirrors train.py encode())
      function vector(): number[] {
        const val = (k: string) => $('in_' + k) as HTMLInputElement;
        const recency = parseFloat(val('recency').value);
        const history = parseFloat(val('history').value);
        const out = $('out_recency'); if (out) out.textContent = recency + ' mo';
        const outh = $('out_history'); if (outh) outh.textContent = '$' + Math.round(history).toLocaleString();
        const zip = val('zip_code').value;
        const chan = val('channel').value;
        return [
          (recency - enc.recency.mean) / enc.recency.std,
          (Math.log1p(history) - enc.history.mean) / enc.history.std,
          val('mens').checked ? 1 : 0,
          val('womens').checked ? 1 : 0,
          val('newbie').checked ? 1 : 0,
          zip === 'Urban' ? 1 : 0,
          zip === 'Rural' ? 1 : 0,
          chan === 'Web' ? 1 : 0,
          chan === 'Multichannel' ? 1 : 0,
        ];
      }

      const score = (m: any, v: number[]) => {
        let z = m.intercept;
        data.columns.forEach((c: string, i: number) => { z += m.coef[c] * v[i]; });
        return sig(z);
      };

      const QUAD: Record<string, { label: string; action: string }> = {
        persuadable: { label: 'Persuadable', action: 'Send the email. This visit happens only because you reached them.' },
        sure:        { label: 'Sure Thing', action: 'Skip it. They were going to visit anyway, so the email is wasted spend.' },
        lost:        { label: 'Lost Cause', action: 'Skip it. Unlikely to visit whether you email or not.' },
        sleeping:    { label: 'Sleeping Dog', action: 'Do not email. Reaching them actually lowers their chance of visiting.' },
      };

      function compute() {
        const v = vector();
        const pt = score(data.models.treat, v);
        const pc = score(data.models.control, v);
        const up = pt - pc;

        $('pTreat').textContent = pct(pt);
        $('pCtrl').textContent = pct(pc);
        const upEl = $('pUplift');
        upEl.textContent = (up >= 0 ? '+' : '') + pct(up);
        upEl.className = 'prob-num uplift ' + (up < -0.002 ? 'neg' : up > 0.002 ? 'pos' : 'flat');

        // uplift bar: center is zero, range roughly +/- 12pp
        const fill = $('upbarFill') as HTMLElement;
        const frac = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, up / 0.12));
        fill.style.left = frac >= 0 ? '50%' : (50 + frac * 50) + '%';
        fill.style.width = Math.abs(frac) * 50 + '%';
        fill.dataset.dir = up < -0.002 ? 'neg' : 'pos';

        let q: string;
        if (up < -0.002) q = 'sleeping';
        else if (pc >= thr) q = 'sure';
        else if (pt >= thr) q = 'persuadable';
        else q = 'lost';

        $('quad').textContent = QUAD[q].label;
        $('action').textContent = QUAD[q].action;
        ($('verdictCard') as HTMLElement).dataset.q = q;
        document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.qcell').forEach((c) => {
          c.classList.toggle('active', c.dataset.q === q);
        });
      }

      compute();
    }

    main();
  </script>

  <style>
    .up { position: relative; z-index: 2; padding: clamp(28px, 6vw, 64px) var(--pad-x) 120px; }
    .up-container { width: 100%; max-width: 1080px; margin-inline: auto; }
    .back {
      display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: clamp(32px, 6vw, 56px); transition: color .25s;
    }
    .back:hover { color: var(--lilac); }

    .up-title {
      font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700;
      font-size: clamp(34px, 6vw, 68px); letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.02; margin-bottom: 22px;
    }
    .up-lead { font-size: clamp(16.5px, 1.3vw, 19px); color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 800px; }
    .up-lead strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
    .up-lead em { color: var(--lilac); font-style: normal; }
    .up-lead a { color: var(--purple-lt); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
    .tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 26px; }
    .tag {
      font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 12px; padding: 5px 13px; border-radius: 7px;
      background: rgba(168,85,247,0.05); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-dim);
    }

    .banner {
      margin: 28px 0 0; padding: 13px 18px; border-radius: 11px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--lilac);
      background: rgba(232,121,249,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(232,121,249,0.24);
    }
    .banner code { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; color: var(--magenta); }

    .block-h { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 30px); letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .block-sub { color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 24px; max-width: 460px; line-height: 1.7; }
    .block-sub em { color: var(--lilac); font-style: normal; }

    /* Demo */
    .demo { margin-top: clamp(48px, 7vw, 76px); }
    .demo-inner {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.05fr; gap: clamp(24px, 4vw, 52px);
      padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 34px); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 20px;
      background: linear-gradient(165deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.022), rgba(168,85,247,0.02));
    }
    .fields { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px 22px; align-content: start; }
    .field { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; font-size: 13.5px; }
    .field-top { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; color: var(--text-dim); }
    .field-top output { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; color: var(--lilac); font-size: 13px; }
    .field-toggle { flex-direction: row; align-items: center; gap: 10px; color: var(--text-dim); cursor: pointer; grid-column: span 2; }
    .field-toggle input { width: 16px; height: 16px; accent-color: var(--purple); cursor: pointer; }
    input[type=range] { -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none; width: 100%; height: 4px; border-radius: 3px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--violet), var(--purple)); outline: none; }
    input[type=range]::-webkit-slider-thumb { -webkit-appearance: none; width: 16px; height: 16px; border-radius: 50%;
      background: #fff; border: 3px solid var(--purple); cursor: pointer; box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(168,85,247,0.2); }
    input[type=range]::-moz-range-thumb { width: 15px; height: 15px; border-radius: 50%; background: #fff; border: 3px solid var(--purple); cursor: pointer; }
    .select {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text);
      border-radius: 9px; padding: 9px 11px; font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 14px;
    }
    .select:focus { border-color: rgba(168,85,247,0.5); outline: none; }

    .demo-right { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
    .verdict-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 22px 24px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); transition: border-color .3s, background .3s;
    }
    .verdict-card[data-q="persuadable"] { border-color: rgba(52,211,153,0.5); background: rgba(52,211,153,0.06); }
    .verdict-card[data-q="sure"]        { border-color: rgba(168,85,247,0.4); background: rgba(168,85,247,0.05); }
    .verdict-card[data-q="lost"]        { border-color: var(--border); }
    .verdict-card[data-q="sleeping"]    { border-color: rgba(244,63,94,0.5); background: rgba(244,63,94,0.06); }
    .verdict-quad { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 34px); letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
    .verdict-card[data-q="persuadable"] .verdict-quad { color: #34d399; }
    .verdict-card[data-q="sleeping"] .verdict-quad { color: #fb7185; }
    .verdict-card[data-q="sure"] .verdict-quad { color: var(--lilac); }
    .verdict-action { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--text-dim); line-height: 1.6; margin: 6px 0 18px; }

    .probs { display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 10px; }
    .prob-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px; flex: 1; }
    .prob-num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 26px); line-height: 1; color: var(--text); }
    .prob-num.uplift.pos { color: #34d399; }
    .prob-num.uplift.neg { color: #fb7185; }
    .prob-num.uplift.flat { color: var(--muted); }
    .prob-cap { font-size: 11px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.3; }
    .prob-cap strong { color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 600; }
    .prob-op { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 20px; color: var(--muted); padding-bottom: 14px; }

    .upbar { position: relative; height: 8px; border-radius: 5px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); margin-top: 18px; overflow: hidden; }
    .upbar-zero { position: absolute; left: 50%; top: 0; bottom: 0; width: 1px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); z-index: 2; }
    .upbar-fill { position: absolute; top: 0; height: 100%; border-radius: 5px; transition: left .3s var(--ease), width .3s var(--ease); }
    .upbar-fill[data-dir="pos"] { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #a855f7, #34d399); }
    .upbar-fill[data-dir="neg"] { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f43f5e, #fb7185); }

    .quad-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 20px 22px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
    .quad-head { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .quad-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; }
    .qcell { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 11px; padding: 12px 13px; transition: border-color .25s, background .25s; }
    .qcell span { display: block; font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .qcell small { font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.4; }
    .qcell small em { color: var(--lilac); font-style: normal; }
    .qcell[data-q="persuadable"].active { border-color: rgba(52,211,153,0.6); background: rgba(52,211,153,0.08); }
    .qcell[data-q="persuadable"].active span { color: #34d399; }
    .qcell[data-q="sure"].active { border-color: rgba(168,85,247,0.5); background: rgba(168,85,247,0.07); }
    .qcell[data-q="sure"].active span { color: var(--lilac); }
    .qcell[data-q="lost"].active { border-color: rgba(148,140,173,0.5); background: rgba(148,140,173,0.06); }
    .qcell[data-q="lost"].active span { color: var(--text); }
    .qcell[data-q="sleeping"].active { border-color: rgba(244,63,94,0.6); background: rgba(244,63,94,0.08); }
    .qcell[data-q="sleeping"].active span { color: #fb7185; }
    .quad-foot { font-size: 11.5px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 14px; line-height: 1.6; }

    /* Results */
    .results { margin-top: clamp(56px, 8vw, 92px); }
    .tiles { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 14px; margin: 22px 0 34px; }
    .tile { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
    .tile-num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: clamp(26px, 3.4vw, 34px); color: var(--lilac); }
    .tile-cap { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 4px; }
    .tile-cap span { display: block; opacity: 0.7; font-size: 11px; }
    .charts { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 18px; }
    .chart { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
    .chart img { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
    .chart figcaption { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted); padding: 10px 14px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); line-height: 1.5; }
    .charts-note { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--muted); }
    .charts-note code { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; color: var(--lilac); }

    /* Method */
    .method { margin-top: clamp(56px, 8vw, 92px); }
    .steps { margin: 18px 0 0; padding-left: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.65; }
    .steps strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }
    .repo { margin-top: 32px; }
    .btn {
      display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 14px;
      padding: 12px 22px; border-radius: 10px; color: var(--text);
      border: 1px solid rgba(168,85,247,0.4); background: rgba(168,85,247,0.08); transition: all .25s;
    }
